Tribal rebels in southwest Pakistan killed three soldiers and injured seven in an attack on a paramilitary convoy.
Violence escalated in Baluchistan after a rocket attack on a gas plant in January.
The Baluchistan Liberation Army claimed responsibility for some attacks.
Clashes between tribal rebels and Pakistani troops left up to 30 dead and 70 injured.
Thousands fled Dera Bugti amid fears of renewed clashes.
Armed tribesmen surrounded paramilitary troops, leading to a tense standoff.
The conflict also resulted in the deaths of 17 Hindu minorities and significant property damage.
